{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":474,"text":"Other people. Everyone is interested in other people."},{"time":3283,"text":"Everyone has relationships with other people,"},{"time":5406,"text":"and they're interested in these relationships"},{"time":6998,"text":"for a variety of reasons."},{"time":8853,"text":"Good relationships, bad relationships,"},{"time":10865,"text":"annoying relationships, agnostic relationships,"},{"time":14011,"text":"and what I'm going to do is focus on the central piece"},{"time":17435,"text":"of an interaction that goes on in a relationship."},{"time":20738,"text":"So I'm going to take as inspiration the fact that we're all"},{"time":23074,"text":"interested in interacting with other people,"},{"time":25499,"text":"I'm going to completely strip it of all its complicating features,"},{"time":29331,"text":"and I'm going to turn that object, that simplified object,"},{"time":33225,"text":"into a scientific probe, and provide the early stages,"},{"time":37375,"text":"embryonic stages of new insights into what happens"},{"time":39824,"text":"in two brains while they simultaneously interact."}]},{"cues":[{"time":43474,"text":"But before I do that, let me tell you a couple of things"},{"time":45767,"text":"that made this possible."},{"time":47466,"text":"The first is we can now eavesdrop safely"},{"time":50247,"text":"on healthy brain activity."},{"time":52958,"text":"Without needles and radioactivity,"},{"time":55535,"text":"without any kind of clinical reason, we can go down the street"},{"time":58398,"text":"and record from your friends' and neighbors' brains"},{"time":61525,"text":"while they do a variety of cognitive tasks, and we use"},{"time":64063,"text":"a method called functional magnetic resonance imaging."},{"time":67797,"text":"You've probably all read about it or heard about in some"},{"time":70122,"text":"incarnation. Let me give you a two-sentence version of it."},{"time":74500,"text":"So we've all heard of MRIs. MRIs use magnetic fields"},{"time":77984,"text":"and radio waves and they take snapshots of your brain"},{"time":80013,"text":"or your knee or your stomach,"},{"time":82374,"text":"grayscale images that are frozen in time."},{"time":84419,"text":"In the 1990s, it was discovered you could use"},{"time":86740,"text":"the same machines in a different mode,"},{"time":89399,"text":"and in that mode, you could make microscopic blood flow"},{"time":91745,"text":"movies from hundreds of thousands of sites independently in the brain."},{"time":95045,"text":"Okay, so what? In fact, the so what is, in the brain,"},{"time":98245,"text":"changes in neural activity, the things that make your brain work,"},{"time":102077,"text":"the things that make your software work in your brain,"},{"time":104087,"text":"are tightly correlated with changes in blood flow."},{"time":106576,"text":"You make a blood flow movie, you have an independent"},{"time":108549,"text":"proxy of brain activity."}]},{"cues":[{"time":110888,"text":"This has literally revolutionized cognitive science."},{"time":113922,"text":"Take any cognitive domain you want, memory,"},{"time":115913,"text":"motor planning, thinking about your mother-in-law,"},{"time":118054,"text":"getting angry at people, emotional response, it goes on and on,"},{"time":121769,"text":"put people into functional MRI devices, and"},{"time":124858,"text":"image how these kinds of variables map onto brain activity."},{"time":128241,"text":"It's in its early stages, and it's crude by some measures,"},{"time":131090,"text":"but in fact, 20 years ago, we were at nothing."},{"time":133658,"text":"You couldn't do people like this. You couldn't do healthy people."},{"time":136017,"text":"That's caused a literal revolution, and it's opened us up"},{"time":138505,"text":"to a new experimental preparation. Neurobiologists,"},{"time":141323,"text":"as you well know, have lots of experimental preps,"},{"time":145083,"text":"worms and rodents and fruit flies and things like this."},{"time":148224,"text":"And now, we have a new experimental prep: human beings."},{"time":151621,"text":"We can now use human beings to study and model"},{"time":155382,"text":"the software in human beings, and we have a few"},{"time":158332,"text":"burgeoning biological measures."}]},{"cues":[{"time":161167,"text":"Okay, let me give you one example of the kinds of experiments that people do,"},{"time":165054,"text":"and it's in the area of what you'd call valuation."},{"time":167731,"text":"Valuation is just what you think it is, you know?"},{"time":169866,"text":"If you went and you were valuing two companies against"},{"time":172670,"text":"one another, you'd want to know which was more valuable."},{"time":175406,"text":"Cultures discovered the key feature of valuation thousands of years ago."},{"time":179285,"text":"If you want to compare oranges to windshields, what do you do?"},{"time":181975,"text":"Well, you can't compare oranges to windshields."},{"time":184331,"text":"They're immiscible. They don't mix with one another."},{"time":186586,"text":"So instead, you convert them to a common currency scale,"},{"time":188937,"text":"put them on that scale, and value them accordingly."},{"time":191643,"text":"Well, your brain has to do something just like that as well,"},{"time":195079,"text":"and we're now beginning to understand and identify"},{"time":197567,"text":"brain systems involved in valuation,"},{"time":199704,"text":"and one of them includes a neurotransmitter system"},{"time":202336,"text":"whose cells are located in your brainstem"},{"time":204968,"text":"and deliver the chemical dopamine to the rest of your brain."},{"time":208143,"text":"I won't go through the details of it, but that's an important"},{"time":210585,"text":"discovery, and we know a good bit about that now,"},{"time":212742,"text":"and it's just a small piece of it, but it's important because"},{"time":214972,"text":"those are the neurons that you would lose if you had Parkinson's disease,"},{"time":218247,"text":"and they're also the neurons that are hijacked by literally"},{"time":220263,"text":"every drug of abuse, and that makes sense."},{"time":222495,"text":"Drugs of abuse would come in, and they would change"},{"time":224831,"text":"the way you value the world. They change the way"},{"time":226620,"text":"you value the symbols associated with your drug of choice,"},{"time":229819,"text":"and they make you value that over everything else."}]},{"cues":[{"time":232333,"text":"Here's the key feature though. These neurons are also"},{"time":235354,"text":"involved in the way you can assign value to literally abstract ideas,"},{"time":238855,"text":"and I put some symbols up here that we assign value to"},{"time":240896,"text":"for various reasons."},{"time":243616,"text":"We have a behavioral superpower in our brain,"},{"time":246305,"text":"and it at least in part involves dopamine."},{"time":248058,"text":"We can deny every instinct we have for survival for an idea,"},{"time":252247,"text":"for a mere idea. No other species can do that."},{"time":256252,"text":"In 1997, the cult Heaven's Gate committed mass suicide"},{"time":259858,"text":"predicated on the idea that there was a spaceship"},{"time":262073,"text":"hiding in the tail of the then-visible comet Hale-Bopp"},{"time":265858,"text":"waiting to take them to the next level. It was an incredibly tragic event."},{"time":270130,"text":"More than two thirds of them had college degrees."},{"time":273615,"text":"But the point here is they were able to deny their instincts for survival"},{"time":277338,"text":"using exactly the same systems that were put there"},{"time":280204,"text":"to make them survive. That's a lot of control, okay?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":284246,"text":"One thing that I've left out of this narrative"},{"time":286335,"text":"is the obvious thing, which is the focus of the rest of my"},{"time":288569,"text":"little talk, and that is other people."},{"time":290728,"text":"These same valuation systems are redeployed"},{"time":293724,"text":"when we're valuing interactions with other people."},{"time":296216,"text":"So this same dopamine system that gets addicted to drugs,"},{"time":299487,"text":"that makes you freeze when you get Parkinson's disease,"},{"time":302011,"text":"that contributes to various forms of psychosis,"},{"time":305088,"text":"is also redeployed to value interactions with other people"},{"time":309008,"text":"and to assign value to gestures that you do"},{"time":311904,"text":"when you're interacting with somebody else."}]},{"cues":[{"time":314478,"text":"Let me give you an example of this."},{"time":317055,"text":"You bring to the table such enormous processing power"},{"time":320022,"text":"in this domain that you hardly even notice it."}]},{"cues":[{"time":322646,"text":"Let me just give you a few examples. So here's a baby."},{"time":324113,"text":"She's three months old. She still poops in her diapers and she can't do calculus."},{"time":327843,"text":"She's related to me. Somebody will be very glad that she's up here on the screen."},{"time":331196,"text":"You can cover up one of her eyes, and you can still read"},{"time":333572,"text":"something in the other eye, and I see sort of curiosity"},{"time":336327,"text":"in one eye, I see maybe a little bit of surprise in the other."}]},{"cues":[{"time":339924,"text":"Here's a couple. They're sharing a moment together,"},{"time":343103,"text":"and we've even done an experiment where you can cut out"},{"time":344421,"text":"different pieces of this frame and you can still see"},{"time":347428,"text":"that they're sharing it. They're sharing it sort of in parallel."},{"time":349932,"text":"Now, the elements of the scene also communicate this"},{"time":352395,"text":"to us, but you can read it straight off their faces,"},{"time":354630,"text":"and if you compare their faces to normal faces, it would be a very subtle cue."}]},{"cues":[{"time":358133,"text":"Here's another couple. He's projecting out at us,"},{"time":361480,"text":"and she's clearly projecting, you know,"},{"time":364368,"text":"love and admiration at him."}]},{"cues":[{"time":366631,"text":"Here's another couple. (Laughter)"},{"time":370266,"text":"And I'm thinking I'm not seeing love and admiration on the left. (Laughter)"},{"time":375416,"text":"In fact, I know this is his sister, and you can just see"},{"time":377976,"text":"him saying, \"Okay, we're doing this for the camera,"},{"time":380489,"text":"and then afterwards you steal my candy and you punch me in the face.\" (Laughter)"},{"time":386191,"text":"He'll kill me for showing that."}]},{"cues":[{"time":388297,"text":"All right, so what does this mean?"},{"time":391094,"text":"It means we bring an enormous amount of processing power to the problem."},{"time":394444,"text":"It engages deep systems in our brain, in dopaminergic"},{"time":398092,"text":"systems that are there to make you chase sex, food and salt."},{"time":400910,"text":"They keep you alive. It gives them the pie, it gives"},{"time":403804,"text":"that kind of a behavioral punch which we've called a superpower."}]},{"cues":[{"time":406708,"text":"So how can we take that and arrange a kind of staged"},{"time":410362,"text":"social interaction and turn that into a scientific probe?"},{"time":413060,"text":"And the short answer is games."},{"time":415751,"text":"Economic games. So what we do is we go into two areas."},{"time":420155,"text":"One area is called experimental economics. The other area is called behavioral economics."},{"time":423491,"text":"And we steal their games. And we contrive them to our own purposes."},{"time":427569,"text":"So this shows you one particular game called an ultimatum game."},{"time":430536,"text":"Red person is given a hundred dollars and can offer"},{"time":432381,"text":"a split to blue. Let's say red wants to keep 70,"},{"time":436104,"text":"and offers blue 30. So he offers a 70-30 split with blue."},{"time":440190,"text":"Control passes to blue, and blue says, \"I accept it,\""},{"time":443041,"text":"in which case he'd get the money, or blue says,"},{"time":444997,"text":"\"I reject it,\" in which case no one gets anything. Okay?"},{"time":449304,"text":"So a rational choice economist would say, well,"},{"time":452696,"text":"you should take all non-zero offers."},{"time":454752,"text":"What do people do? People are indifferent at an 80-20 split."},{"time":458514,"text":"At 80-20, it's a coin flip whether you accept that or not."},{"time":462038,"text":"Why is that? You know, because you're pissed off."},{"time":464929,"text":"You're mad. That's an unfair offer, and you know what an unfair offer is."},{"time":468538,"text":"This is the kind of game done by my lab and many around the world."},{"time":471242,"text":"That just gives you an example of the kind of thing that"},{"time":473786,"text":"these games probe. The interesting thing is, these games"},{"time":477524,"text":"require that you have a lot of cognitive apparatus on line."},{"time":481231,"text":"You have to be able to come to the table with a proper model of another person."},{"time":484159,"text":"You have to be able to remember what you've done."},{"time":487372,"text":"You have to stand up in the moment to do that."},{"time":488792,"text":"Then you have to update your model based on the signals coming back,"},{"time":492142,"text":"and you have to do something that is interesting,"},{"time":495114,"text":"which is you have to do a kind of depth of thought assay."},{"time":497711,"text":"That is, you have to decide what that other person expects of you."},{"time":501044,"text":"You have to send signals to manage your image in their mind."},{"time":503998,"text":"Like a job interview. You sit across the desk from somebody,"},{"time":506851,"text":"they have some prior image of you,"},{"time":508220,"text":"you send signals across the desk to move their image"},{"time":510971,"text":"of you from one place to a place where you want it to be."},{"time":514891,"text":"We're so good at this we don't really even notice it."},{"time":518276,"text":"These kinds of probes exploit it. Okay?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":522043,"text":"In doing this, what we've discovered is that humans"},{"time":523850,"text":"are literal canaries in social exchanges."},{"time":526181,"text":"Canaries used to be used as kind of biosensors in mines."},{"time":529578,"text":"When methane built up, or carbon dioxide built up,"},{"time":533138,"text":"or oxygen was diminished, the birds would swoon"},{"time":537324,"text":"before people would -- so it acted as an early warning system:"},{"time":539650,"text":"Hey, get out of the mine. Things aren't going so well."},{"time":542630,"text":"People come to the table, and even these very blunt,"},{"time":545584,"text":"staged social interactions, and they, and there's just"},{"time":548574,"text":"numbers going back and forth between the people,"},{"time":551590,"text":"and they bring enormous sensitivities to it."},{"time":553789,"text":"So we realized we could exploit this, and in fact,"},{"time":556478,"text":"as we've done that, and we've done this now in"},{"time":559034,"text":"many thousands of people, I think on the order of"},{"time":561728,"text":"five or six thousand. We actually, to make this"},{"time":563893,"text":"a biological probe, need bigger numbers than that,"},{"time":566117,"text":"remarkably so. But anyway,"},{"time":569791,"text":"patterns have emerged, and we've been able to take"},{"time":571795,"text":"those patterns, convert them into mathematical models,"},{"time":575631,"text":"and use those mathematical models to gain new insights"},{"time":578320,"text":"into these exchanges. Okay, so what?"},{"time":580451,"text":"Well, the so what is, that's a really nice behavioral measure,"},{"time":583764,"text":"the economic games bring to us notions of optimal play."},{"time":587083,"text":"We can compute that during the game."},{"time":589567,"text":"And we can use that to sort of carve up the behavior."}]},{"cues":[{"time":592520,"text":"Here's the cool thing. Six or seven years ago,"},{"time":596850,"text":"we developed a team. It was at the time in Houston, Texas."},{"time":599400,"text":"It's now in Virginia and London. And we built software"},{"time":602794,"text":"that'll link functional magnetic resonance imaging devices"},{"time":606001,"text":"up over the Internet. I guess we've done up to six machines"},{"time":610036,"text":"at a time, but let's just focus on two."},{"time":612017,"text":"So it synchronizes machines anywhere in the world."},{"time":615075,"text":"We synchronize the machines, set them into these"},{"time":618244,"text":"staged social interactions, and we eavesdrop on both"},{"time":620227,"text":"of the interacting brains. So for the first time,"},{"time":621893,"text":"we don't have to look at just averages over single individuals,"},{"time":625500,"text":"or have individuals playing computers, or try to make"},{"time":628397,"text":"inferences that way. We can study individual dyads."},{"time":631160,"text":"We can study the way that one person interacts with another person,"},{"time":633945,"text":"turn the numbers up, and start to gain new insights"},{"time":636509,"text":"into the boundaries of normal cognition,"},{"time":639024,"text":"but more importantly, we can put people with"},{"time":641756,"text":"classically defined mental illnesses, or brain damage,"},{"time":645093,"text":"into these social interactions, and use these as probes of that."},{"time":648644,"text":"So we've started this effort. We've made a few hits,"},{"time":650994,"text":"a few, I think, embryonic discoveries."},{"time":653443,"text":"We think there's a future to this. But it's our way"},{"time":656255,"text":"of going in and redefining, with a new lexicon,"},{"time":658815,"text":"a mathematical one actually, as opposed to the standard"},{"time":662837,"text":"ways that we think about mental illness,"},{"time":665415,"text":"characterizing these diseases, by using the people"},{"time":667482,"text":"as birds in the exchanges. That is, we exploit the fact"},{"time":670489,"text":"that the healthy partner, playing somebody with major depression,"},{"time":674733,"text":"or playing somebody with autism spectrum disorder,"},{"time":677643,"text":"or playing somebody with attention deficit hyperactivity disorder,"},{"time":681493,"text":"we use that as a kind of biosensor, and then we use"},{"time":684712,"text":"computer programs to model that person, and it gives us"},{"time":687356,"text":"a kind of assay of this."}]},{"cues":[{"time":689826,"text":"Early days, and we're just beginning, we're setting up sites"},{"time":691957,"text":"around the world. Here are a few of our collaborating sites."},{"time":695367,"text":"The hub, ironically enough,"},{"time":697676,"text":"is centered in little Roanoke, Virginia."},{"time":700565,"text":"There's another hub in London, now, and the rest"},{"time":702834,"text":"are getting set up. We hope to give the data away"},{"time":706843,"text":"at some stage. That's a complicated issue"},{"time":710516,"text":"about making it available to the rest of the world."},{"time":713510,"text":"But we're also studying just a small part"},{"time":715357,"text":"of what makes us interesting as human beings, and so"},{"time":717624,"text":"I would invite other people who are interested in this"},{"time":719665,"text":"to ask us for the software, or even for guidance"},{"time":722234,"text":"on how to move forward with that."}]},{"cues":[{"time":724453,"text":"Let me leave you with one thought in closing."},{"time":726794,"text":"The interesting thing about studying cognition"},{"time":728736,"text":"has been that we've been limited, in a way."},{"time":732468,"text":"We just haven't had the tools to look at interacting brains"},{"time":735411,"text":"simultaneously."},{"time":736611,"text":"The fact is, though, that even when we're alone,"},{"time":739081,"text":"we're a profoundly social creature. We're not a solitary mind"},{"time":743192,"text":"built out of properties that kept it alive in the world"},{"time":747565,"text":"independent of other people. In fact, our minds"},{"time":751513,"text":"depend on other people. They depend on other people,"},{"time":754383,"text":"and they're expressed in other people,"},{"time":755924,"text":"so the notion of who you are, you often don't know"},{"time":759576,"text":"who you are until you see yourself in interaction with people"},{"time":762264,"text":"that are close to you, people that are enemies of you,"},{"time":764670,"text":"people that are agnostic to you."},{"time":767215,"text":"So this is the first sort of step into using that insight"},{"time":770991,"text":"into what makes us human beings, turning it into a tool,"},{"time":774286,"text":"and trying to gain new insights into mental illness."},{"time":776264,"text":"Thanks for having me. (Applause)"},{"time":779385,"text":"(Applause)"}]}]}